---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Delete Your Account | 282 Munro Bagging App"
  description="How to permanently delete your 282 account and all associated data from within the app."
  path="/delete-account"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-8 sm:px-6">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'Delete Your Account' }]} />
    <article class="prose prose-gray mt-6">
      <h1>How to Delete Your 282 Account</h1>
      <p>
        This guide provides step-by-step instructions on how to delete your 282 account. Please
        read through each step carefully to understand the implications of deleting your account.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Data loss:</strong> deleting your 282 account will permanently delete all the
          data associated with it, including your completions, posts, photos, and any other data
          stored in 282 services.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Recovery:</strong> once deleted, your account cannot be recovered.</li>
        <li><strong>Account check:</strong> ensure you are deleting the correct account.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Steps to delete your account</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Sign in:</strong> open 282 and tap the Profile tab, then sign in with the account
          you wish to delete.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open settings:</strong> tap the settings icon on the right-hand side.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Delete your account:</strong> tap <em>Delete Account</em>, then confirm by
          tapping <em>Delete</em> in the pop-up to permanently delete your account.
        </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For further assistance, email
        <a href="mailto:alastair.r.mcneill@gmail.com">alastair.r.mcneill@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</Base>
